comments: Mills (SAS) and Porzingis (DAL) mutually engage in marginal arm to arm contact off ball.
Gay (SAS) takes a step towards Doncic (DAL) but he stops short and establishes a legal guarding position. Doncic seeks out the body contact during his jump shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) swipes down and makes contact with the ball as Johnson (SAS) attempts to gather the rebound.
Doncic (DAL) makes marginal contact with DeRozan (SAS) during his driving shot attempt.

Johnson (SAS) and Brunson (DAL) both place a hand on the ball which results in a correctly called jump ball situation. Following the whistle, Johnson's shoulder makes incidental contact to Brunson's head/face. The crew communicated with the Replay Center and determined that no additional penalties would be assessed and that the ball did not hit the rim.
Aldridge's (SAS) arm makes incidental contact to Porzingis' (DAL) head as he extends it and makes contact with the loose ball.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor is overturned to Spurs ball.
DeRozan's (SAS) draws Porzingis (DAL) towards him and the body contact affects DeRozan's SQBR during his pass attempt.
DeRozan (SAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Mills (SAS) makes marginal leg to leg contact to Doncic (DAL) when he changes directions during his drive at the 00:22.0 mark.  Doncic moves through the marginal contact and continues his drive.
During the shot attempt, Johnson (SAS) and Porzingis (DAL) make incidental foot to foot contact.  As Porzingis falls to the floor, he makes incidental contact with DeRozan's (SAS) leg.
Gay (SAS) commits a take foul on Brunson (DAL).
DeRozan (SAS) commits a take foul on Porzingis (DAL).
Johnson (SAS) commits a take foul on Iwundu (DAL).
